    "what_description": "Coelogyne carnea is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae, native to the tropical regions of Southeast Asia. It is a terrestrial orchid with a sympodial habit, producing long, slender stems that are 20-50 cm in height and 1-2 cm in diameter. The leaves are alternate, lanceolate, and 10-20 cm in length, with a leathery texture and a waxy sheen. The inflorescence is a raceme of 5-10 flowers, each 3-4 cm in diameter, with a red-brown lip and a white or yellowish column. The flowers have a distinctive shape, with a prominent keel and a crenulate margin, and are highly fragrant, emitting a sweet, floral scent.",
