    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Coelogyne carnea improperly include headache, nausea, dizziness, and these symptoms can be caused by improper handling, excessive exposure to plant toxins, or allergic reactions to its sap or pollen. Coelogyne carnea contains toxic compounds such as alkaloids and glycosides that can cause irritation to the skin, eyes, and respiratory system if not handled carefully. If ingested, these toxins can induce nausea, vomiting, and dizziness due to their emetic and vasodilatory properties. In some cases, exposure to Coelogyne carnea can lead to more severe reactions, such as headaches and dizziness, which can be triggered by an allergic response or an overreaction of the immune system. It is essential to handle Coelogyne carnea with caution and follow proper safety guidelines to minimize the risk of adverse side effects.",
